However, this `ErrorCompat` trait is not implemented for all implementors of `std::error::Error`. I want to — in some generic error printing code — be able to display the chain of causes along with the stacktrace associated with where the SNAFU error was instantiated. Unfortunately, the [`source()`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/std/error/trait.Error.html#method.source) function returns `&amp;(dyn Error + &#39;static)`.

